RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FACT OR FICTION chased briefly then cleared SIR LOOKING GLASS to take control, padded the lead off the rail through the turn, remained clear into the final furlong and held well under a drive. MIDNIGHT LOVE bumped with inner rival at the start, chased three wide into the turn, moved out on the turn and entered the lane six wide, drifted in while finishing willingly through the final furlong but could only whittle the gap on the winner. PUDDIN HEAD JONES bumped at the start, raced near the inside on the back into the turn, came out and exited the bend five wide, offered a mild rally and gained the show. NED bumped with outer rival in the beginning, got put in a bit tight chasing between rivals early, had to steady approaching the three-eighths pole, angled in leaving the bend and could not rally. SIR LOOKING GLASS broke well then chased the leader up the backstretch, raced along the inside into the turn, moved out and spun five wide into the stretch, then weakened down the lane. BLACKJACK AND BEER broke in and bumped, raced outside a rival into the turn near the back, drifted out on the turn, moved inward midstretch to bother rival and failed to menace. T G I F ALPHA brushed leaving the gate then dropped back, trailed four wide into the turn, got floated out midway around the bend, angled in some late on the bend and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Blackjack and Beer
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in/bumped, drifted out turn, angled in, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Sir Looking Glass
ENTRY.OWNER: Handwerk Mathew Kessler Tom Kruljac J Eric Lewkowitz Frank Lewkowitz Karen May R

ENTRY.NAME: Ned
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, bit tight early, steadied 3/8, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, chased 3-6wide, drifted in, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: T G I F Alpha
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4wide, floated out tur, angled in, steadied midstretch, no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 91. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELWOOD BLUES chased from inside briefly then switched to the outside of the pacesetter, went up to apply pressure, headed rival around the bend, got forced out and bumped by DON CORLEONE late on the bend, vied with inner pair at the top of the stretch, dueled with HEY BROTHER into the final furlong and drew clear late. HEY BROTHER broke a step slow, chased off the pace then moved closer into the turn, rounded the bend two then three wide, bid inside at the top of the lane, dueled with ELWOOD BLUES to the sixteenth pole, yielded late but managed to hold second. DEVILISH DESIRE tossed his head up and came away last, trailed on the inside through the turn, came with a mild rally along the fence but could not get by HEY BROTHER for second. SNEAK A SMILE broke a step slow, chased off the pace two wide leaving the backstretch, spun five wide into the lane and lacked a rally. DON CORLEONE stepped to the front and set the tone early, moved over to the inside, challenged from outside around the bend, started to drift out then lugged out and bumped ELWOOD BLUES leaving the bend, fought between to midstretch and weakened in the furlong grounds. ANNIVERSAIRE D'OR forwardly place from outside early, went three wide into the turn, moved out wider around the bend, angled outside the top pair at the top of the stretch and weakened. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION THE HALF-MILE FRACTION WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Devilish Desire
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, inside, mild rail rally

ENTRY.NAME: Elwood Blues
ENTRY.OWNER: Pegram Michael E Watson Karl and Weitman Paul
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased, pressed outside, forced out/bumped turn, dueled, best

ENTRY.NAME: Anniversaire d'Or
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, 3-6wide, angled out into str, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Hey Brother
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, chased 2-3wide, dueled str, held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 83. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIFF WITH JIMMY quickly cleared, kicked away two, three, then four wide on the turn, asked left handed midstretch and continued to widen under steady handling. YVETT'S SURPRISE chased three wide into the turn, entered the lane five wide, could not make any headway on the winner but was clearly second best. STORMING GRAY chased five wide into the turn, got moved out to the six path briefly, steered in a bit to enter the lane four wide, lacked a serious response but churned on for a clear third. TAKE CARAMIE broke a step slow, closest in pursuit along the rail into the turn, eased off the fence and exited the bend four wide but weakened down the lane. FEVER broke well then dropped back to last, saved ground through the turn and was not a factor. LIGHTS ASTERN chased between rivals well off the rail, went four then five wide on the turn before angling down to the two path leaving the bend and came up empty.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 84. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY PARTNER GLEN climbed early while chasing three deep into the first turn, went five wide into the far turn, came six wide into the stretch, rallied from the middle portion of the track, collared the leader at the sixteenth pole and drove past. TOKAMAK vied four deep into the first turn then chased four wide into the backstretch, stalked two wide into the far turn, angled out and bid five wide into the stretch, kicked clear in upper stretch, headed at the sixteenth pole and yielded late. AVIATOR NATION broke a step slow, traveled four then three deep on the first turn, went four wide into the second bend, moved in a bit then angled five wide into the stretch, kept on through the lane and edged IVORY SKY for the show. IVORY SKY was off slow to begin, raced along the inside at the back into the first turn, stayed inside to the second bend, eased off the rail and came three wide into the stretch, angled out in the lane, summoned a mild rally but was outkicked for the show honors. VENOM bobbled leaving the gate, vied between into the first turn then took a stalking position behind the top pair, traveled along the rail then two wide leaving the far turn and lacked a bid. NYQUILER vied three deep into the clubhouse turn then dueled from outside, fought into the stretch and weakened. I GOT A GUY vied along the rail then dueled inside NYQUILER, roused around the far turn, fought three wide into the stretch and also weakened. DIAMONDS PREFERRED raced between at the back into the first turn, traveled three wide into the second bend, entered the lane five wide and failed to menace. REEF CITY tracked four in the four path, two to three wide on the second bend, came up empty in the lane and was not persevered with in the furlong grounds. CHURCHMEISTER chased two to three wide on the first turn, angled over to the rail on the second bend and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Ivory Sky
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, inside-3wide 2nd, angled out, mild rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 26000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIKE OPERATOR sprinted clear early and showed the way in the two path around the first turn, led three wide into the lane, put to right handed urging in upper stretch, felt SIGNOFTHECROSS gaining into the final furlong but responded well to hold that rival at bay. SIGNOFTHECROSS bumped inner rival at the start, chased five wide into the first turn then angled to the three path, remained three wide to the far turn, spun five wide into the stretch, drew closer from outside in the lane and loomed boldly at the eighth pole but lacked the needed late kick to get by the winner. PACO'S PICO bumped leaving the gate, chased four wide outside a rival on the clubhouse turn, remained wide into the lane and could not summon the needed response in the final furlong. EGOMANIA chased on the inside, got put in a bit tight near the three-eighths pole and dropped back to last, angled six wide into the lane and kept on for a minor award. MY INDY chased in the two path, angled over to the rail on the far turn and lacked a rally. SOL DEL SUR closest in pursuit off the rail around the first turn, rounded the far turn two to three wide and tired.

ENTRY.OWNER: A and J Racing and R and K Racing

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, 4wide into str, no response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 97. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ISSA COURT stumbled leaving the gate, raced up close in the two path, moved up to press from outside at the four furlong mark, took over at the three-eighths pole, drifted five wide leaving the far turn, responded when called upon with the right hand while continuing to drift out and held gamely to the wire. CORNELIA FORT forwardly placed three deep on the first turn, bid outside the new leader on the second bend, got floated out by that rival six wide leaving the far turn, hounded that rival from outside while also drifting out but could not summon the needed late kick to overtake the winner. TIZZY TWISTER settled in the two path, rounded the far turn four wide, fought with WARRIOR LADY for the show honors and bested that rival for a minor award. WARRIOR LADY stalked along the rail, moved out and went four wide into the second bend, came six wide into the lane and got outdueled for the show honors. SWEET HELLO set the pace from inside, pressured at the half-mile pole, lost command with three furlongs remaining, chased the top pair past the five-sixteenths pole, came out into the lane and gave way. HOT ROD MAMA dropped back early and tucked inside, saved ground to the stretch and failed to menace.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED CROSS KNIGHT showed the way in the two path early, pressure from outer pair into the backstretch, maintained a short lead around the far turn then cleared approaching the stretch, felt some pressure from RODRIGOKNOWS at the top of the stretch but responded nicely when called upon and drew away in the late stages. RODRIGOKNOWS chased keenly along the inside early, took aim three wide into the lane, loomed in upper stretch but was turned away by the winner. BUCK OWENS chased four wide into the far turn, two then three wide on the second bend, churned on for the show honors but could not threaten the top pair. DISCRETIONARY DAY chased two to three wide early, went two, three, then four wide on the second bend, angled out in the lane and lacked a rally. STAR PROSPECT chased three then four wide early, stayed off the inside into the second bend, moved into the three path then steered five wide into the lane and weakened. NOLONGERAHOBBY settled inside early then shifted to the two path to go between rivals on the first turn, tipped three wide to go up and pressure the leader into the backstretch, kept the pressure on through the far turn, lost touch with the leader and chased four wide approaching the stretch, then weakened in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Starlet S. - Grade2 LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 93. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR TWO YEAR OLD FILLIES. By subscription of $500 each to accompany the nomination on or before August 31st, 2023 closed with 31. For all horses not nominated, supplementary nominations of $7,500 each will close at the time of entry closed with 1. All hor ses shall pay $1,500 to pass the entry box and $2,500 additional to start, with $200,000 Guaranteed, with $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. 120 lbs.A trophy will be presented to the winning owner, trainer and jockey. iner and jockey. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOTHING LIKE YOU vied for the lead inside a trio of rivals into the clubhouse turn then took control around the bend, cleared CHATALAS on the backstretch, pressured by that rival into the far turn, shook free again around the bend, showed the way in the two path entering the lane, roused at the top of the stretch, kicked away midstretch, asked once right handed in the final furlong and coasted in the final sixteenth. GREAT FORTY EIGHT bobbled a bit at the start, hustled between rivals early, dropped back a bit to chase two wide then along the rail on the clubhouse turn, saved ground through the second bend, shifted out ad bumped CHATALAS midstretch and kept on willingly for a clear second. FLYNN'S CHANCE hit the gate then settled outside a rival at the back, inched closer on the backstretch, ridden along three wide into the lane, moved out further but flattened out while earning the show honors. CHATALAS vied three deep then two wide on the first turn, stalked NOTHING LIKE YOU on the backstretch then pressed from outside past the half-mile pole, failed to sustain the challenge on the far turn and chased three wide into the lane, got bumped and impeded by GREAT FORTY EIGHT midstretch and weakened in deep stretch. PACIFIC ROSE traveled along the inside racing at the back early, stayed along the fence into the far turn, tipped out leaving that bend and failed to menace. GRAZIA showed early speed four deep then moved into the three path chasing after the top pair on the first turn, navigated the far turn four then three wide and tired. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED GREAT FORTY EIGHT FROM SECOND AND PLACED HER FOURTH FOR SHIFTING OUT AND CAUSING INTERFERENCE TO CHATALAS IN MIDSTRETCH, COSTING THAT RIVAL A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING.
